===Etymology===
From the surname of the inventor, [[w:Frank Zamboni|Frank J. Zamboni]], and his brand of such machines.

{{trademark erosion|en|Zamboni|[http://www.zamboni.com/copyright.html#trademark Frank J. Zamboni & Co. Inc.]}}

The surname itself is of {{der|en|it|-}} origin, as a northeastern dialectal variant (possibly {{der|en|vec|-}}) of {{m|it|Giambono}}, comprised of a reduced form of {{m|it|Gianni}} (from {{m|it|Giovanni||John}}) + {{m|it|Bono}} or {{m|it|buono||good}}. Frank Zamboni's father originated from {{w|Arsio}} in {{w|Trentino}}, northern Italy.

